## Sentry (error monitoring)

Production errors are captured with `@sentry/nextjs` (client, server, edge via `instrumentation*.js` / `sentry.*.config.js`, and `pages/_error.js`). Config is in `next.config.mjs` via `withSentryConfig`.

**Plan:** Developer (free) ‚Äî roughly 5k errors/month, 1 user, **email** alerts. Third-party alert integrations (e.g. Slack) and Seer require a paid plan; don‚Äôt assume they‚Äôre available.

**Env (Vercel Production only ‚Äî never hardcode):**

- `NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN` ‚Äî required for reporting
- `SENTRY_ORG` / `SENTRY_PROJECT` / `SENTRY_AUTH_TOKEN` ‚Äî optional; auth token is for source-map upload (mark sensitive in Vercel)

SDK is production-only and uses a low `tracesSampleRate` to stay within free-plan limits. Do not enable Session Replay unless the plan and quota allow it.

**When debugging production bugs:** Check [Sentry Issues](https://sketchplanations.sentry.io/issues/) first. Browser/DOM noise (e.g. `removeChild` with no frames in `pages/` or `components/`) is often safe to archive or ignore.

**Resolving via GitHub (optional):** Include `Fixes SKETCHPLANATIONS-XX` in a commit or PR body (issue short ID from Sentry) so Sentry can mark it resolved after the fix ships. Don‚Äôt strip Sentry wiring without intent.
